{
  "stem": "25651.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But my mother and this lady were sort of thinking that these two kids belong together.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somehow, we-- it-- it was understood that they were thinking of us as a couple.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I mean, we were children of five or something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the way that we fell apart with this Helen, Helen [NON-ENGLISH]-- she's alive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She lives in, in Australia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she married a religious Jew, and she's become religious, and I'm completely [INAUDIBLE] [LAUGHS] so-- But the way that we broke up was when-- we broke up when we were five, so the match never, the match which my mother was planning never came to anything.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because my mother wasn't sure that I would like skiing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She thought that I'd get scared and be timid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So she bought the skis, and she-- she bought the boots because the boots were good anyway for the winter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the binding was a sort of child's binding, which was like a sandal, so that you could take ordinary, high, good boots and ski.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But she wasn't going to buy the skiing trousers, because-- she was going to buy the skiing trousers only after she saw that I would, that I would ski.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the skiing trial-- I always had hand-me-downs from, from my brothers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH] skiing trousers were too large for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So she borrowed the skiing trousers of this girl Helen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it didn't have buttons, you see.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were not boys', boys' trousers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I refused to wear them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she said, well, you can't go skiing, then, because you've got to have skiing trousers for the snow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We used to have very deep snow in Novy Jicin, big, powdery drifts of snow.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
